  "notes": [
    "This configuration resolves City of Glendale base zoning by intersecting coordinates with Layer 0 of the official public Glendale Zoning feature service.",
    "The configured test coordinate at State Farm Stadium resolves to A-1, Agricultural, in the published zoning layer.",
    "BASE_ZONE is used as the primary zoning code; ZONING is retained as a fallback and as the published combined-zoning value.",
    "LEDEND is the actual field name published by the service and contains the zoning district label.",
    "OVERLAY, CONDITIONA, Z_CASES, and PENDING are retained when published because they may identify supplemental zoning review requirements.",
    "The City of Glendale states that its online zoning maps are informational and are not the final authority; zoning confirmation is available from the Planning Department Planner of the Day.",
    "Glendale's Unified Development Code became effective January 12, 2024; a resolved zoning result does not replace review of the current UDC, overlays, zoning cases, conditions, pending actions, or confirmation by the City of Glendale."
  ]
